{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review & amend school attendance guidance on the \u201cS\u201d code & introduce a new code",
        "additional_details": "We feel by not marking children\u2019s attendance as \u201cLeft\u201d or having attendance concluded, they are marked with the \u201cS\u201d code, indicating an absence due to study leave. This S code counts as an absence**, which can dramatically affect the student\u2019s overall attendance percentage. This could negatively affect how parents view their child\u2019s record, and in some cases, may impact students.",
        "background": "We urge the Government to review & amend the S code which grants students study leave for exams, so that it is excluded from negatively affecting attendance rates. We also urge the Government to introduce a clear code (e.g. L \u2013 Left or C \u2013 Completed Education) that won't affect attendance statistics",
